#Approach:

Approach:
Ye code infix ko prefix me convert karne ke liye reverse + postfix logic use karta hai.

1. Sabse pehle poori string reverse karte hain.
2. Reverse karne ke baad '(' ko ')' aur ')' ko '(' me change kar dete hain.
3. Ab is reversed expression par almost infix to postfix wala logic apply karte hain:
   - operand aaye to answer me add karo
   - '(' aaye to stack me push karo
   - ')' aaye to '(' tak sab pop karke answer me add karo
   - operator aaye to precedence ke according stack handle karo
4. End me stack ke bache operators answer me add kar do.
5. Jo answer mila hai wo reversed prefix hota hai, isliye last me usse reverse kar dete hain.

Main idea:
Infix → Prefix directly karna thoda tricky hota hai,
isliye code pehle expression reverse karta hai, phir postfix jaisa process chala ke final answer reverse kar deta hai.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(n)

#Code:

class Solution {

    public int priority(Character a){
        if(a == '^'){
            return 2;
        }
        else if(a == '*' || a == '/'){
            return 1;
        }
        else if(a == '+' || a == '-'){
            return 0;
        }
        else{
            return -1;
        }
    }

    public String infixToPrefix(String s) {
        // Your code goes here
        StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder(s);
        StringBuilder ans = new StringBuilder();

        //Step 1: reverse the string and make the opeining bracket as closing and vice versa
        sb.reverse();

        for(int i=0; i<sb.length(); i++){
            char ch = sb.charAt(i);
            if(ch == '('){
                sb.setCharAt(i, ')');
            }
            else if(ch == ')'){
                sb.setCharAt(i, '(');
            }
        }

        int i = 0;
        int n = sb.length();
        ArrayDeque<Character> stack = new ArrayDeque<>();

        while(i<n){

            
            char ch = sb.charAt(i);
            //If space
            if(sb.charAt(i) == ' '){
                continue;
            }
            //if i is an operand
            else if((ch >= 'A' && ch <= 'Z') || (ch >= 'a' && ch <= 'z') || (ch >= '0' && ch <= '9')){
                ans.append(sb.charAt(i));
            }

            //if i is an opening bracket
            else if(ch == '('){
                stack.push(sb.charAt(i));
            }

            //if i is a closing bracket
            else if(ch == ')'){
                while(!stack.isEmpty() && stack.peek() != '('){
                    ans.append(stack.pop());
                }
                stack.pop();
            }
            //if i is an operator
            else{
                while(!stack.isEmpty() && priority(sb.charAt(i)) < priority(stack.peek())){
                    ans.append(stack.pop());
                }
                stack.push(sb.charAt(i));
            }
            i++;
        }

        while(!stack.isEmpty()){
            ans.append(stack.pop());
        }

        ans.reverse();
        return ans.toString();


    }
}
